                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "The morale of this sordid tale is unAfrican in its context, the king shall not die in his palace surrounded by his subjects who \x{201c}adore\x{201d} him but in a non-descript expensive hospital room surrounded by strangers.",
                                   'sentence_number' => 9,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '487'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'A king that fails to rule with probity will die in a distance in disgrace with everyone breathing a long sigh of relief - Good riddance!',
                                   'sentence_number' => 10,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '488'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'To them all.',
                                   'sentence_number' => 11,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '489'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "Togolese blogger Rodrigue Kopgli, of Jeunesse Unie pour la D\x{e9}mocratie en Afrique [Fr], called Bongo \x{201c}one of the last crocodiles of Fran\x{e7}afrique \x{201c}: Ami de tous les gouvernements fran\x{e7}ais depuis De Gaulle, Albert-Bernard Bongo devenu El Hadj Omar Bongo puis Ondimba (le peuple lui r\x{e9}clame du changement d\x{e9}mocratique, il lui offre des changements de nom personnel), n\x{2019}a jamais cess\x{e9} d\x{2019}\x{ea}tre l\x{2019}Agent des Services secrets fran\x{e7}ais qu\x{2019}il \x{e9}tait \x{e0} sa prise du pouvoir.",
                                   'sentence_number' => 12,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '490'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "Fort de sa long\x{e9}vit\x{e9} et de la fortune amass\x{e9}e au sommet du Gabon, Le Hadj s\x{2019}octroie le luxe de financer des campagnes \x{e9}lectorales en France notamment celle de Fran\x{e7}ois Mitterrand comme l\x{2019}a \x{e9}crit Pierre P\x{e9}an dans \x{ab} Affaires africaines \x{bb}.",
                                   'sentence_number' => 13,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '491'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "Il laisse aussi un gigantesque parc mobilier et immobilier en France et des comptes bancaires secrets qui bien \x{e9}videmment font et feront le bonheur des paradis fiscaux qui les h\x{e9}bergent.",
                                   'sentence_number' => 14,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '492'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'Le peuple gabonais pendant ce temps manque de tout.',
                                   'sentence_number' => 15,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '493'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "Avec un tel bilan, la terre ne lui sera pas l\x{e9}g\x{e8}re du tout.",
                                   'sentence_number' => 16,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '494'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "Et les Africains qu\x{2019}il pr\x{e9}tendait cyniquement repr\x{e9}senter ne se mettront pas en deuil, non plus.",
                                   'sentence_number' => 17,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '495'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'Friend of all French governments since De Gaulle, Albert-Bernard Bongo, who later became El Hadj Omar Bongo and then Ondimba (the people were asking for democratic change, he offered them personal name changes), he never stopped being the French secret service agent that he had been since he came to power.',
                                   'sentence_number' => 18,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '496'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "With his longevity and fortune amassed in power, the Hadj afforded himself the luxury of financing electoral campaigns in France, in particular that of Fran\x{e7}ois Mitterrant as written by Pierre P\x{e9}an in \x{201c}African Affairs\x{201d}.",
                                   'sentence_number' => 19,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '497'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'He\'s also leaving gigantic real estate assets and private property in France, and secret bank accounts that are making the tax havens where they are hosted very happy.',
                                   'sentence_number' => 20,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '498'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'Meanwhile, the Gabonese people are lacking everything.',
                                   'sentence_number' => 21,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '499'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'With this legacy, he will not be missed at all.',
                                   'sentence_number' => 22,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '500'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'And the Africans that he was cynically pretending to represent will not mourn him either.',
                                   'sentence_number' => 23,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '501'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "Citing Togo's experience, Kopgli doubts Bongo's death will bring change: La mort de Bongo n\x{2019}apportera rien de salutaire au peuple gabonais, car les h\x{e9}ritiers Ali et Pascaline Bongo sont d\x{e9}j\x{e0} positionn\x{e9}s et port\x{e9}s par Bollor\x{e9} \x{2013} ami personnel de Sarkozy \x{2013} et de Christophe de Margerie de TotalFinaElf et de bien d\x{2019}autres vampires pour capter le pouvoir, comme ce fut le cas du Togo o\x{f9} les fils du d\x{e9}funt Gnassingbe ont \x{e9}t\x{e9} port\x{e9}s au pouvoir sous le double poids du viol et des violences.",
                                   'sentence_number' => 24,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '502'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "Bongo's death is not going to bring anything beneficial to the Gabonese people, because the heir and heiress Ali and Pascaline Bongo have already been groomed and brought by Bollor\x{e9} -personal friend of Sarkozy- and of Christophe de Margerie of TotalFinaElf and many other vampires to suck power, as it was the case in Togo where the children of the late Gnassingbe were brought to power under the double weight of rape and violence.",
                                   'sentence_number' => 25,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '503'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "Ivorian blogger Th\x{e9}ophile Kouamouo [Fr], who also mentions Togo, ponders about what will happen after Bongo's death and wonders about the future of the Fran\x{e7}afrique : Maintenant que le \x{201c}patriarche\x{201d} n'est plus, l'on entre dans l'\x{e8}re des incertitudes et des questionnements.",
                                   'sentence_number' => 26,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '504'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "Le sch\x{e9}ma constitutionnel - remise du pouvoir \x{e0} la pr\x{e9}sidente du S\x{e9}nat puis \x{e9}lections - sera-t-il respect\x{e9} ?",
                                   'sentence_number' => 27,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '505'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "Va-t-on vers un sch\x{e9}ma de bataille fratricide \x{e0} la togolaise [...]?",
                                   'sentence_number' => 28,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '506'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "L'arm\x{e9}e gabonaise, totalement invisible, entrera-t-elle en sc\x{e8}ne ?",
                                   'sentence_number' => 29,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '507'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "Puis profond\x{e9}ment, quel est le bilan d'Omar Bongo Ondimba ?",
                                   'sentence_number' => 30,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '508'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "Apr\x{e8}s sa mort, la Fran\x{e7}afrique, dont il \x{e9}tait le pilier, s'affaiblira-t-elle ?",
                                   'sentence_number' => 31,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '509'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "Pour ma part, je pense que oui - mais peut-\x{ea}tre que je m'avance trop.",
                                   'sentence_number' => 32,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '510'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "Ce syst\x{e8}me-l\x{e0} \x{e9}tait trop centr\x{e9} sur un certain nombre d'hommes, de petits secrets, de r\x{e8}gles de d\x{e9}part qui n'existent plus, pour perdurer \x{e9}ternellement.[...]",
                                   'sentence_number' => 33,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '511'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "La Fran\x{e7}afrique s'affaiblira, mais la d\x{e9}mocratie avancera-t-elle ?",
                                   'sentence_number' => 34,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '512'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "L'Afrique se retrouvera bient\x{f4}t face \x{e0} son destin et aux contradictions de son Histoire.",
                                   'sentence_number' => 35,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '513'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "Personne ne l'aidera \x{e0} en d\x{e9}m\x{ea}ler les noeuds.",
                                   'sentence_number' => 36,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '514'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'Mais observons d\'abord ce qui se passera dans les prochains jours au Gabon.',
                                   'sentence_number' => 37,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '515'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "Now that the \x{201c}patriarch\x{201d} has passed away, we are entering an era of uncertainty and questioning.",
                                   'sentence_number' => 38,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '516'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'The constitutional outline -power transfer to the President of the Senate and then elections-, is it going to be respected?',
                                   'sentence_number' => 39,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '517'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'Are we going to fall into fratricidal fighting like in Togo [...]?',
                                   'sentence_number' => 40,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '518'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'Is the Gabonese army, completely invisible, going to enter the scene?',
                                   'sentence_number' => 41,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '519'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'More profoundly, what is the legacy of Omar Bongo Odinma?',
                                   'sentence_number' => 42,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '520'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "After his death, is the Fran\x{e7}afrique, of which he was the pillar, going to weaken?",
                                   'sentence_number' => 43,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '521'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'Personally, I think so - but maybe I\'m getting ahead of myself.',
                                   'sentence_number' => 44,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '522'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'This system was too focused on certain men, on little secrets, on exit rules that don\'t exist anymore, to last forever. [...]',
                                   'sentence_number' => 45,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '523'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "Fran\x{e7}afrique will grow weaker, but will democracy move forward?",
                                   'sentence_number' => 46,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '524'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'Africa will soon be faced to its own destiny and to the contradictions of its history.',
                                   'sentence_number' => 47,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '525'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'Nobody will help her to untie the knots.',
                                   'sentence_number' => 48,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '526'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'But let\'s first observe what will happen in the next days in Gabon.',
                                   'sentence_number' => 49,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '527'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'fr',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => "Emmanuel Bellart of Cameroon [Fr] expressed his relief: Dieu merci, car un autre est parti, l'afrique commence \x{e0} respirer petit \x{e0} petit, il ne fallait plus que \x{e7}a pour que l'afrique puisse finalement ouvrir les yeux, monsieur omar bongo qui a mit 41 ans au pouvoir, ce qui est iraisonnable nous a montr\x{e9} combien ces vieux de la france voulaient vraiment detruire l'afrique, c'est claire que personne ne doit souhaiter la mort d'un \x{ea}tre humain, mais d'un c\x{f4}t\x{e9}, c'est un soulagement pour le peuple gabonais, sauf qu'il y'avait une chose que monsieur bongo devait faire, c'est organiser le pouvoir et non de le preparer pour ses enfants [...] adieu le doyen, laissons le pouvoir au peuple et non \x{e0} une personne, quand tu t'accapare du pouvoir , tu meurs et on t'oublit Thank God, another one is gone and Africa is starting to breathe little by little.",
                                   'sentence_number' => 50,
                                   'stories_id' => 10,
                                   'story_sentences_id' => '528'
                                 },
                                 {
                                   'db_row_last_updated' => '2014-07-19 15:48:10.482566-05',
                                   'language' => 'en',
                                   'media_id' => 1,
                                   'publish_date' => '2009-06-08 05:50:18',
                                   'sentence' => 'That\'s all we needed for Africa to be able to open her eyes at last.',
